      "description": "Available is a benchmark-example 2002 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54B32 3.2L inline-six. This specimen exhibits exceptional mechanical health with a recently overhauled dual-VANOS system and a reinforced rear subframe to ensure structural integrity. The Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox offers precise gate selection, feeding power through a perfectly operational M-variable differential lock. Technical highlights include synchronized individual throttle bodies (ITBs), factory-spec compression across all cylinders, and a pristine suspension geometry with all-original bushings showing zero signs of degradation. Finished in Titanium Silver Metallic with an immaculate undercarriage, this M3 represents the pinnacle of naturally aspirated performance and chassis balance.",
